obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be called "The Bombay Revenue Jurisdiction Act, 1876".`
  line
  line `Commencement.--So much of section four as relates to claims to set aside, on the ground of`
  line `irregularity, mistake or any other ground except fraud, sales for arrears of land-revenue, shall come into`
  line `force on such day as the Governor General in Council directs in that behalf by notification in the Gazette`
  line `of India. The rest of this Act shall come into force on the passing thereof:`
  line
  line `Extent.--And it shall extend to all ^1[the ^2[State of Maharashtra]], but not so as to affect--`
  line
  line `(a) any suit regarding the assessment of revenue on land situate in ^3[the City of Bombay], or the collection of such revenue;`
  line
  line `(b) any of the provisions of Bombay Acts 5 of 1862 and 6 of 1862, or of ^4[Act 21 of 1881] or of Act 23 of 1871;`
  line
  line `^5* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the Adaptation of law 1950, for "all the territories under the Government of the Governor of Bombay in Council".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the Adaptation of law 1960, for "State of Bombay".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by, s. 9 of the Greater Bombay Laws and the Bombay High Court (Declaration of Limits) Act, 1945 (Bom. 17 of 1945), Schedule E. read with Bom. 52 of 1947, s. 2 proviso, for "the Collectorate of Bombay".`
  line
  line `4. Rep. by Act 12 of 1891, the Second Schedule Part 1.`
  line
  line `5. Rep. by Act 16 of 1895, the First Schedule (w.e.f. 10-10-1895).`
