  sectionId (44274)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Interpretation-clause.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_187610_1550814354714&sectionId=44274&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_187610_1550814354714
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there be something repugnant in the subject or`
  line context,--
  line
  line `"Land" includes the sites of villages, towns and cities: it also includes trees, growing crops`
  line `and grass, fruit upon, and juice in, trees, rights-of-way, ferries, fisheries, and all other benefits to arise out`
  line `of land, and things attached to the earth, or permanently fastened to things attached to the earth:`
  line
  line `"Land-revenue" means all sums and payments, in money or in kind, received or claimable by or on behalf ^1[of the ^2[Government]] from any person on account of any land held ^3[by ^4[ State] Government] under the provisions of any law for the time being in force::`
  line
  line `"Revenue officer" means any officer employed in or about the business of the`
  line `land-revenue, or of the surveys, assessment, accounts or records connected therewith.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the Adaptation of Indian Laws Order in Council, for "of the Crown".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws Order, 1950, for "Crown".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the Adaptation of Indian Laws Order in Council, for “by the Provincial Government”.`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws Order, 1950, for “Provincial”.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (44275)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Bar of certain suits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_187610_1550814354714&sectionId=44275&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_187610_1550814354714
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the exceptions hereinafter appearing, no Civil Court shall`
  line `exercise jurisdiction as to any of the following matters:--`
  line
  line `(a) ^1[claims against the ^2[Government] relating to any property appertaining to the office of any`
  line `hereditary officer appointed or recognized under Bombay Act No. 3 of 1874, or any other law for the`
  line `time being in force, or of any other village-officer or servant, or`
  line
  line `claims to perform the duties of any such officer or servant, or in respect of any injury caused by`
  line `exclusion from such office or service, or`
  line
  line `suits to set aside or avoid any order under the same Act or any other law relating to the same`
  line `subject for the time being in force passed ^3[by the ^4[State] Government] or any officer duly authorized in that behalf, or`
  line
  line `claims against Government relating to lands held under treaty, or to lands granted or held as saranjam, or on other political tenure, or to lands declared by Government or any officer duly authorized in that behalf to be held for service;`
  line
  line `(b) objections--`
  line
  line `to the amount or incidence of any assessment of land-revenue authorized ^3[by the ^4[State]`
  line `Government], or`
  line
  line `to the mode of assessment, or to the principle on which such assessment is fixed, or`
  line
  line `to the validity or effect of the notification of survey or settlement, or of any notification`
  line `determining the period of settlement;`
  line
  line `(c) claims connected with or arising out of any proceedings for the realization of land-revenue or`
  line `the rendering of assistance ^3[by the ^4[State] Government] or any officer duly authorized in that behalf to superior holders or occupants for the recovery of their dues from inferior holders or tenants;`
  line
  line `claims to set aside on account of irregularity, mistake, or any other ground except fraud, sales for`
  line `arrears of land-revenue;`
  line
  line `(d) claims against ^2[Government]--`
  line
  line `(1) to be entered in the revenue survey or settlement records or village papers as liable for the`
  line `land-revenue, or as superior holder, inferior holder, occupant or tenant, or`
  line
  line `(2) to have any entry made in any record of a revenue survey or settlement, or`
  line
  line `(3) to have any such entry either omitted or amended;`
  line
  line `(e) the distribution of land or allotment of laud-revenue on partition of any estate under Bombay`
  line `Act 4 of 1868, or any other law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(f) ^1[claims against ^2[Government]]--`
  line
  line `to hold land wholly or partially free from payment of land-revenue, or`
  line
  line `to receive payments charged on or payable out of the land-revenue, or`
  line
  line `to set aside any cess or rate authorized ^3[by the ^4[State] Government] under the provisions of`
  line `any law for the time being in force, or`
  line
  line `respecting, the occupation of waste or vacant land belonging ^5[to the ^2[Government]];`
  line
  line `(g) claims regarding boundaries fixed under Bombay Act No. 1 of 1865, or any other law for the`
  line `time being in force, or to set aside any order passed by a competent officer under any such law with`
  line `regard to boundary-marks:`
  line
  line `Proviso.--Provided that if any person claim to hold land wholly or partially exempt from`
  line `payment of land-revenue under--`
  line
  line `(h) any enactment for the time being in force expressly creating an exemption not before existing`
  line `in favour of an individual or of any class of persons, or expressly confirming such an exemption on`
  line `the ground of its being shown in a public record, or of its having existed for a specified term of years,`
  line or
  line
  line `(i) an instrument or sanad given by or by order of the ^3[ ^4[State] Government] under Bombay Act No. 2 of 1863, section one, clause first, or Bombay Act No. 7 of 1863, section two, clause first, or`
  line
  line `(j) any other written grant by the British Government expressly creating or confirming such`
  line `exemption, or`
  line
  line `(k) a judgment by a Court of law, or an adjudication duly passed by a competent officer under`
  line `Bombay Regulation 17 of 1827, chapter X, or under Act No. 11 of 1852, which declares the`
  line `particular property in dispute to be exempt;`
  line
  line `such claim shall be cognizable in the Civil Courts.`
  line
  line `Illustrations to (h).`
  line
  line `(1) It is enacted that, in the event of the proprietary right in lands, the property of Government, being`
  line `transferred to individuals, they shall be permitted to hold the lands for ever at the assessment at which they are`
  line `transferred. The proprietary right in certain lands is transferred to A at an assessment of Rs. 100. An exemption from`
  line `higher assessment not before existing is expressly created in favour of A by enactment, and he may seek relief in`
  line `the Civil Court against over-assessment.`
  line
  line `(2) It is enacted that when a specific limit to assessment has been established and preserved, the assessment`
  line `shall not exceed such specific limit. A is the owner of land worth Rs. 100 for assessment. He claims to be assessed`
  line `at Rs. 50 only on the strength of a course of dealing with him and his predecessors under which his land has not been`
  line `more highly assessed. There is no exemption not before existing created by enactment, and A's claim is not`
  line `cognizable in a Civil Court.`
  line
  line `(3) It is enacted that land-revenue shall not be leviable from any land held and entered in the land-registers as`
  line `exempt. A claims to hold certain land as exempt on the ground that it has been so held by him, and is so entered in`
  line `the land-register. This is an exemption expressly confirmed by enactment on the ground of its being shown in a`
  line `public record, and A's claim is cognizable in a Civil Court.`
  line
  line `(4) It is enacted that the Collector shall confirm existing exemptions of all lands shown in certain maps to be exempt. A claims exemption alleging that his land is shown in the maps to be exempt. A's claim is cognizable in a`
  line `Civil Court.`
  line
  line `(5) It is enacted that assessment shall be fixed with reference to certain considerations, and not with reference to`
  line `others. This is not an enactment creating an exemption in favour of any individual or class, and no objection to an`
  line `assessment under such an enactment is cognizable in a Civil Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the Adaptation of Indian Laws Order in Council, for “claims against the Crown”.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws Order, 1950, for “Crown”.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the Adaptation of Indian Laws Order in Council, for “by the Provincial Government”.`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws Order, 1950, for “Provincial”.`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by the Adaptation of Indian Laws Order in Council for “to the Crown”.`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by the Adaptation of Indian Laws order in Council, for “Provincial Government”.`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws Order, 1950, for “Provincial”`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (44276)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Saving of certain suits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_187610_1550814354714&sectionId=44276&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_187610_1550814354714
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in section four shall be held to prevent the Civil Courts from entertaining the following suits:--`
  line
  line `(a) suits ^1[against the ^2[Government]] to contest the amount claimed, or paid under protest, or`
  line `recovered, as land-revenue on the ground that such amount is in excess of the amount authorized in`
  line `that behalf ^3[by the ^4[State] Government], or that such amount had previous to such claim, payment, or recovery been satisfied, in whole or in part, or that the plaintiff, or the person whom he represents, is not the person liable for such amount;`
  line
  line `(b) suits between private parties for the purpose of establishing any private right, although it may`
  line `be affected by any entry in. any record of a revenue survey or settlement or in any village papers;`
  line
  line `(c) suits between superior holders or occupants and inferior holders or tenants regarding the dues`
  line `claimed or recovered from the latter;`
  line
  line `and nothing in section four, clause (g) shall be held to prevent the Civil Courts from entertaining suits, other than suits ^1[against the ^2[Government]], for possession of any land being a whole survey number or a recognized share of a survey number.`
  line
  line `^5[and nothing in section four shall be held to prevent the Civil Courts in the Districts mentioned in the second schedule hereto annexed from exercising such jurisdiction as, according to the terms of any law in force on the twenty-eighth day of March 1876, they could have exercised over claims ^1[against the ^2[Government]]--`
  line
  line `(a) relating to any property appertaining to the office of any hereditary officer appointed or`
  line `recognized under Bombay Act No. 3 of 1874, or any other law for the time being in force, or of`
  line `any other village-officer or servant;`
  line
  line `(b) to hold land wholly or partially free from payment of land-revenue;`
  line
  line `(c) to receive payments charged on, or payable out of, the land-revenue.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the Adaptation of Indian Laws Order in Council, for "against the Crown".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws Order 1950, for "Crown".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the Adaptation of Indian Laws Order in Council, for "by the Provincial Government".`
  line
  line `4.Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws Order, 1950, for "Provincial".`
  line
  line `5. Added by Act 16 of 1877, s. 1 (w.e.f. 9-8-1877).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (44277)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Bar of certain suits against Revenue officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_187610_1550814354714&sectionId=44277&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_187610_1550814354714
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Revenue officers shall not be liable to be`
  line `sued for damages in any Civil Court for any act bona fide done, or ordered to be done, by them as such in`
  line `pursuance of the provisions of any law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `If any Revenue officer absconds or does not attend when called on by his official superior, and if the`
  line `Collector of the District proceeds against him or his sureties for public money, papers or property`
  line `according to the provisions of any law for the time being in force, such Collector shall not be liable to pay`
  line `damages or costs in any suit brought against him by such officer or sureties, although it appears that a part`
  line `only, or no part whatever, of the sum demanded was due from the officer so absconding or failing to`
  line `attend, or that he was not in possession of the papers or property demanded of him.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (44278)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Punishment or prosecution of Revenue officers not a bar to civil remedies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_187610_1550814354714&sectionId=44278&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_187610_1550814354714
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in any`
  line `law for the time being in force which authorizes the punishment departmentally of any Revenue officer`
  line `for any offence or breach of duty, or which sanctions his prosecution criminally for such offence or`
  line `breach, shall be held to bar any remedy which may be had in the Civil Court against such officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
