  content `[Power to Local Government to call for record.]—Rep. by, s. 2, ibid.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_187610_1550814354714&sectionId=44281&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_187610_1550814354714
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (44282)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Suits not to be entertained unless plaintiff has exhausted right of appeal.`
  content `No Civil Court shall entertain any suit ^1[against the ^2[Government]] on account of any act or omission of any Revenueofficer unless the plaintiff first proves that, previously to bringing his suit, he has presented all such appeals allowed by the law for the time being in force, as within the period of limitation allowed for bringing such suit, it was possible to present.t.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_187610_1550814354714&sectionId=44282&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_187610_1550814354714
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the Adaptation of Indian Laws Order in Council for “against the Crown”.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws Order, 1950, for “Crown”.`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (44283)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Power of State Government to refer questions for decision of High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_187610_1550814354714&sectionId=44283&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_187610_1550814354714
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `12. Power of ^1[State] Government to refer questions for the decision of the High Court.-- If in the trial or investigation of any suit, claim or objection, which, but for the passing of this Act, might have been tried or investigated by a Civil Court, there arises any question on which ^2*** the ^3[ ^1[State] Government] desires to have the decision of the High Court, ^2*** the ^3[ ^1[State] Government] ^4*** may cause a statement of the question to be prepared, and may refer such question for the decision of the High Court ^5***.`
  line
  line `The said High Court shall fix an early day for the hearing of the question referred, and cause notice of such day to be placed in the Court-house.`
  line
  line `The parties to the case may appear and he heard in the High Court in person or by their advocates or pleaders.`
  line
  line `The High Court, when it has heard and considered the case, shall send a copy of its decision, with the reasons therefor, under the seal of the Court, to the Government by which the reference was made, and subject to any appeal which may be presented to ^6[the Supreme Court], the case shall be disposed of conformably to such decision..`
  line
  line `If the High Court considers that any such statement is imperfectly framed, the High Court may return it for amendment.`
  line
  line `The costs (if any) consequent on any such reference shall be dealt with as the High Court in each case directs`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws Order, 1950, for "Provincial".`
  line
  line `2. The words "the Governor General in Council or" omitted by the Adaptation of Indian Laws Order in Council.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by ibid., for "Provincial Government".`
  line
  line `4. The words "as the case may be" were omitted by the Adaptation of Indian Laws Order in Council.`
  line
  line `5. The words "the Governor General in Council or" omitted by the Adaptation of Indian Laws Order in Council.`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws Order, 1950, for "Her Majesty in Council".`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (44284)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Power of Civil Judge to refer questions of jurisdiction to High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws Order, 1950, for “Her Majesty in Council”.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_187610_1550814354714&sectionId=44284&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_187610_1550814354714
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `If in any suit`
  line `instituted, or in any appeal presented, in a Civil Court, the Judge doubts whether he is precluded by this`
  line `Act from taking cognizance of the suit or appeal, he may refer the matter to the High Court.`
  line
  line `The High Court may order the Judge making the reference either to proceed with the case or to return`
  line `the plaint.`
  line
  line `The order of ^1[the Supreme Court] on any such reference shall be subject to appeal to Her Majesty in Council, and save as aforesaid, shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (44285)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Composition of Bench.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_187610_1550814354714&sectionId=44285&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_187610_1550814354714
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Every reference under section twelve or section thirteen shall be heard`
  line `by a Bench consisting of such number of Judges not less than three, as the Chief Justice from time to time`
  line directs.
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
