  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (44287)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Privileges of Government in suits in which it is concerned.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_187610_1550814354714&sectionId=44287&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00005_187610_1550814354714
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Privileges of ^1[Government] ^2*** in suits in which it is concerned.--Whenever any suit is brought in any District Court ^3[against the ^1[Government]] ^2*** or against any Revenue officer, ^4[and the`
  line `^1[Government] ^2*** undertakes] the defence thereof, it shall be lawful ^5[for the ^6[State] Government], by`
  line `certificate signed by a Secretary thereto, to require--`
  line
  line `(a) that such suit shall be tried by the District Judge himself, and shall not be transferred for trial`
  line `to an Assistant Judge; and`
  line
  line `(b) that the trial of any such suit shall have precedence over the trial of any other suit or other`
  line `civil proceeding then pending in such Court;`
  line
  line `and the Court shall give effect to every such requirement.`
  line
  line `The privilege conferred ^7[on Government] by the clause (b) of this section shall, mutatis mutandis, apply to any appeal or special appeal against any decree in any such suit as is described in this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by ibid., for "Crown".`
  line
  line `2. The words "or the Federal Railway Authority" were omitted by the Indian Independence (Adaptation of Central Acts and Ordinances) Order, 1948.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the Adaptation of Indian Laws Order in Council, for "against the Crown or he Federal Railway Authority".`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by ibid., for "and the Crown or the Federal Railway Authority undertakes".`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by ibid, for "for the Provincial Government".`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws Order, 1950, for "Provincial".`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by ibid., for "on the Provincial Government".`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
